the triumph of french grapes in california has been so complete that cabernet sauvignon chardonnay and the rest seem as integral to the state as san francisco fog and malibu mud when california winemakers want to turn to exotica they experiment with italian grapes like sangiovese or barbera by historical standards at least the french grapes should have been the interlopers italian immigrants started many of california 's early winemaking dynasties and their names live on today martini gallo mondavi foppiano and pedroncelli to mention a few yet when the industry came of age its focus was almost wholly on french grapes perhaps because italian wines were held in such low esteem but appreciation for italian wines has risen in the last 25 years barbera the most widely planted grape in the piedmont has most often been used in california as an anonymous blending grape now it is being grown more seriously and bottled on its own sangiovese the prime grape of chianti took up only 186 acres in the whole state in 1990 by 1997 though that figure had risen to almost 2500 acres the highest rate of increase of any red grape in that period according to california wine by james laube wine spectator press 1999 while california sangioveses can vary widely from soft fruity mouthfuls to oaky blasts of tannin i found many to be enjoyable though overpriced and very good with food some of the best versions are made in small quantities bruno d'alfonso the winemaker for sanford winery in santa barbara county makes the excellent di bruno as a side project it is sold in a few stores but is more likely to turn up in restaurants just as the italians have been experimenting with nontraditional blends of grapes to create the wines known as super tuscans so have the californians brewer clifton which makes fine pinot noirs and chardonnays makes a super concentrated blend of sangiovese and merlot under the palmina label while la famiglia robert mondavi 's label for italian varietals recently released its 1997 colmera 80 percent sangiovese blended with five other grapes it too is impressive and will be even more so after it ages a few years di bruno santa barbara county stolpman vineyard 1998 21 rich and concentrated full of earthy fruit and dusty tannins babcock vineyards eleven oaks santa ynez valley 1995 23 aromas of tar dried oranges and rose petals juicy dense flavors swanson napa valley 1997 28 sweet aromas fruity with firm tannins flora springs napa valley 1998 18 spicy aromas with fruit and a spine of acidity gallo sonoma alexander valley barrelli creek vineyards 1997 17 dusky and earthy chocolate aroma with mouth filling tannins rabbit ridge coniglio selezione sonoma county 1997 16 orange and smoke aromas full of fruit but not much depth listed in order of preference prices are those paid in various manhattan wine shops

